<item>
            <title>[LU-8997] lustre-rsync log improvements</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8997</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When lustre-rsync is started in the resume mode &apos;lustre-rsync -l LOG ...&apos; we need to report errors from lr_read_log().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lr_backup_log() should create a hard link to the existing log.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lr_write_log() should create the new log as a temporary file and rename() it onto the (existing) log only if the new log was written successfully.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
